#: ../../source/changelog.rst:11
msgid "8.4.0"
msgstr "8.4.0"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:14
msgid "Requirement and Dependency Changes"
msgstr "要求と依存関係の変更"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:16
msgid "Ren'Py now requires Windows 10 or later to run. This means that it will no longer run on Windows 7, 8, or 8.1."
msgstr "Ren'Py を実行するには Windows 10 以降が必要になりました。つまり Windows 7、8、または8.1では動作しなくなります。"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:18
msgid "Ren'Py now targets Ubuntu 20.04. This also means it targets the \"soldier\" version of the Steam Linux Runtime."
msgstr ""
"Ren'Py は Ubuntu 20.04 をターゲットとしています。これは、Steam Linuxランタイムの \"soldier\" バージョンを対象としていることも意味し"
"ます。"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:20
msgid ""
"Ren'Py is no longer built for 32-bit ARM Linux. This drops support for the Raspberry Pi 3, and very old Chromebooks. Ren'Py is "
"still being built for 32-bit ARM Android. Ren'Py will now prefer the gles2 renderer on ARM Linux devices, such as the Raspberry Pi."
msgstr ""
"Ren'Py は 32 ビット ARM Linux 用にはビルドされなくなりました。これにより、Raspberry Pi 3 と非常に古い Chromebook のサポートが終了し"
"ます。Ren'Py はまだ 32 ビット ARM Android 用にビルドされています。Ren'Py は、Raspberry Pi などの ARM Linux デバイス上で gles2 レン"
"ダラーを優先するようになりました。"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:24
msgid ""
"The Android version of Ren'Py is now being built with 16KB pages, for future Android devices that will require 16 KB page support."
msgstr ""
"Android 版の Ren'Py は、16KB ページのサポートを必要とする将来の Android デバイス向けに、現在 16KB ページでビルドされています。"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:28
msgid "Python 3.12"
msgstr "Python 3.12"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:30
msgid ""
"Ren'Py now uses Python 3.12 on all platforms. This makes avilable several years of Python improvements. To finds all of them, "
"please see:"
msgstr ""
"Ren'Pyは、すべてのプラットフォームでPython 3.12を使用するようになりました。これにより、数年間分の Python の改善が利用可能になりま"
"す。それらすべてを見つけるには、以下を参照してください :"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:33
msgid "`What's New in Python 3.10 <https://docs.python.org/3/whatsnew/3.10.html>`_"
msgstr "`What's New in Python 3.10 <https://docs.python.org/3/whatsnew/3.10.html>`_"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:34
msgid "`What's New in Python 3.11 <https://docs.python.org/3/whatsnew/3.11.html>`_"
msgstr "`What's New in Python 3.11 <https://docs.python.org/3/whatsnew/3.11.html>`_"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:35
msgid "`What's New in Python 3.12 <https://docs.python.org/3/whatsnew/3.12.html>`_"
msgstr "`What's New in Python 3.12 <https://docs.python.org/3/whatsnew/3.12.html>`_"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:37
msgid ""
"One of the most visible changes caused by this is that Ren'Py will now report the location of Python errors at sub-line "
"granularity, rather than at line granularity. In tracebacks, the portions of a line that contribute to an error will be colored or "
"underlined."
msgstr ""
"これによる最も目に見える変更の1つは、Ren'PyがPythonエラーの場所をラインの単位ではなく、サブラインの単位で報告するようになったことで"
"す。トレースバックでは、エラーの原因となる行の部分に色または下線が引かれます。"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:42
msgid "Performance Improvements"
msgstr "パフォーマンスの改善"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:44
msgid ""
"**Script Loading** The internal respresentation of the game script has been changed to reduce the amount of memory used and to "
"improve loading time, by only representing data that varies from the default. For a large game where initial startup is dominated "
"by script loading, this improved the time it takes to load the script by 50%."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:49
msgid ""
"**Persistent Data** The persistent data format has been changed to use numeric hashes of visited script locations, rather than the "
"full script location. These hashes can be saved and loaded much more quickly, which improves game performance when the persistent "
"data is large."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:53
msgid ""
"**OpenGL Drawing** Ren'Py's OpenGL drawing code has been changed to remove allocations of matrix objects, and to reduce the amount "
"of math that needs to be done in many cases. This can improve performance when drawing scenes with large numbers of drawing "
"operations, as those scenes can be CPU-bound."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:57
msgid ""
"Similarly, the OpenGL drawing code has been changed to avoid the repeated allocation of dictionaries that contain shader variables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:60
msgid ""
"**Live2D** When rendering Live2D models, Ren'Py will avoid doing unproductive work to create Renders for layers that are not "
"visible, and masks that are not used. This can improve performance when using Live2D models with many layers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:65
msgid "Shaders"
msgstr "Shaders"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:67
msgid ""
"Ren'Py's GLSL shader support now allows uniforms of types int, bool, ivec2, ivec3, ivec4, and bvec2, bvec3, bvec4, in addition to "
"the support for float, vec2, vec3, vec4, mat2, mat3, mat4 and sampler2D that Ren'Py has always had."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:71
msgid ""
"Ren'Py's GLSL shader support now allows one-dimensions arrays of uniforms of scalar and vector types, but not arrays of  matrices "
"or samplers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:74
msgid ""
"Ren'Py now can supply separate model to world (u_model), world to camera view (u_view), and camera view to viewport (u_projection) "
"matrices to shaders. These matrices are supplied as uniforms. There are also a u_projectionview matrix that combines u_projection "
"and u_view, and the existing u_transform matrix is all three. Breaking these out allows OpenGL shaders to support lighting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:79
msgid ""
"Ren'Py's GLSL shader support now supports performing operations on the underlying data before passing it to a uniform. For "
"example, if ``u_color`` is an RGBA uniform, ``u_color__premul`` is that color, premultiplied by its alpha channel. Other suffixes "
"get the resolution of a texture, and can perform inverse, transpose, and inverse transpose operations on matrices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:84
msgid ""
"Inside Transforms, Ren'Py now supports uniforms of type sampler2D. These are textures that are set up to sample textures. These "
"transforms can be supplied a displayable or a string that becomes a displayable."
msgstr ""
" Ren'Py は Transform 内部での sampler2D 型の uniform をサポートするようになりました。これらは sample テクスチャに設定されるテクス"
"チャです。これらの transform には displayable や displayable になる文字列が供給されます。"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:88
msgid "GLTF Model Loading"
msgstr "GLTF モデルの読み込み"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:90
msgid ""
"Ren'Py now has a minimal ability to load 3D models defined in the GLTF format, using the Open Asset Importer library. Models can "
"be loaded using the :class:`GLTFModel` displayable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:93
msgid ""
"Right now, the GLTFModel loading only supports loading the mesh and textures of a model. There's no support for animation or other "
"features of GLTF. What's more, the default Ren'Py shaders only show the base colors, and a custom shader is required to handle the "
"other portions of physical-based rendering (PBR) that GLTF supports."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:97
msgid ""
"The current GLTFModel support is is likely useful for people who want to use 3D backgrounds in their games, but may require a "
"skilled developer to position the model in 3D space. It's also intended for developers that want to experiment and contribute "
"insights and development back to Ren'Py. A future release will include more tools for working with objects in three dimensions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:103
msgid "Optional Mipmaps"
msgstr "オプションのミップマップ"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:105
msgid ""
"Mipmaps are smaller versions of an image that are used when Ren'Py scales an image down. Using mipmaps prevents the image from "
"becoming jagged when scaled down, but generating mipmaps takes time and can cause the game to use more memory."
msgstr ""
"ミップマップは、Ren'Py が画像を縮小するときに使用される画像の縮小バージョンです。ミップマップを使用すると、縮小したときに画像がギザ"
"ギザになるのを防げますが、ミップマップの生成には時間がかかり、ゲームでより多くのメモリが使用される可能性があります。"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:109
msgid ""
"Ren'Py now leaves the decision of if to create mipmaps to the developer, who knows if the game will scale down an image. By "
"default, Ren'Py will create mipmaps for all images it loas. A new mode will only only create mipmaps when the display is scaled "
"down to less than 75% of the virtual window size. This is suitable for games that do not scale down images, but for which the "
"window size may be smaller than the virtual window size."
msgstr ""
"Ren'Py は、ミップマップを作成するかどうかの決定をゲームが画像を縮小するかどうか分かっている開発者に任せるようになりました。デフォル"
"トでは、 Ren'Py は読み込むすべての画像のミップマップを作成します。新しいモデルでは表示が仮想ウィンドウサイズの 75% 未満に縮小された"
"ときにのみミップマップを作成します。これは画像を縮小しないが、ウィンドウサイズが仮想ウィンドウサイズより小さい可能性があるゲームに"
"適しています。"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:114
msgid "To enable this new mode, set :var:`config.mipmap` to \"auto\"."
msgstr "この新しいモードを有効にするには、 :var:`config.mipmap` を \"auto\" に設定します。"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:116
msgid ""
"Mipmaps will automatically be created for images loaded for the purpose of Live2D or GLTFModel, as these are likely to be scaled "
"down.  Mipmaps can be created for specific images by providing True to the mipmap parameter of :func:`Image`."
msgstr ""
"Live2D や GLTFModel の目的で読み込まれた画像は、縮小される可能性が高いため、ミップマップが自動的に作成されます。 特定の画像に対して"
"ミップマップを作成するには、 :func:`Image` の mipmap パラメータに True を指定します。"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:122
msgid "Libs and Mods"
msgstr "Libs と Mods"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:124
msgid ""
"Ren'Py now includes support for two more special directories, :file:`game/libs` and :file:`game/mods`. These directories are "
"intended to receive third-party libraries and mods, respectively."
msgstr ""
"Ren'Py は、さらに 2 つの特別なディレクトリ、 :file:'game/libs' と :file:'game/mods' のサポートを含むようになりました。これらのディ"
"レクトリは、それぞれサードパーティのライブラリとmodを受け取ることを目的としています。"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:127
msgid ""
"When the file :file:`game/libs/libs.txt` exists, script files inside :file:`game/libs` have the first directory removed, if any, "
"and are loaded in unicode order by the path not including that directory. Similarly, when the file :file:`game/mods/mods.txt` "
"exists, script files inside it are loaded in unicode order by the path, not including that directory."
msgstr ""
"ファイル :file:`game/libs/libs.txt` があれば、 :file:`game/libs` 中のスクリプトファイルは 最初のディレクトリーが除去され、そのディ"
"レクトリーを含まないパスで Unicode 順に読み込まれます。同様に、ファイル :file:`game/mods/mods.txt` があれば、その中のスクリプトファ"
"イルは、そのディレクトリーを含まないパスで Unicode 順に読み込まれます。"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:132
msgid ""
"Note that load order is relatively unimportant in Ren'Py - it's mostly used with :doc:`cds`. Init priorities levels have been "
"changed to recommend that games use init priorities of -99 to 99, and libraries and mods use from -999 to -100 and 100 to 999."
msgstr ""
"Ren'Py ではロード順は主に :doc:`cds` において使用されるのみであり、比較的重要ではないことに注意してください。 init の優先度レベルが"
"変更され、ゲームでは -99 から 99 の init 優先度を使用し、ライブラリと mod では -999 から -100 と 100 から 999 を使用することが推奨"
"されるようになりました。"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:136
msgid ""
"When present, the libs and mods directories are showing in the launcher. The libs directory is created automatically when the game "
"is created. The mods directory can be created manually if a creator wants to support mods."
msgstr ""
"存在する場合、 libs ディレクトーリと mods ディレクトリーがランチャーに表示されます。 libs ディレクトリーは、ゲームの作成時に自動的"
"に作成されます。作成者がmodをサポートしたい場合は、modsディレクトリーを手動で作成できます。"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:139
msgid ""
"The goal of this change is to make it easier to distribute third-party libraries and mods. Instead of needing to be merged with "
"the player's script, a library can be placed under game/libs, and will provide full functionality there."
msgstr ""
"この変更の目的は、サードパーティのライブラリと MOD の配布を容易にすることです。プレイヤーのスクリプトと統合する代わりに、ライブラリ"
"を game/libs の下に配置して、そこで完全な機能を提供できます。"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:142
msgid "`.rpe` and `.rpe.py` files are also searched in the libs directory."
msgstr "`.rpe` ファイルと `.rpe.py` ファイルも libs ディレクトリで検索されます。"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:145 ../../source/changelog.rst:5685
msgid "Layered Images"
msgstr "レイヤー画像"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:147
msgid ""
"The ``variant`` and ``prefix`` properties, which accepted any value but evaluated it (as a string) only at init time, now accept "
"an unquoted `image name component` (digits, letters and underscores, no space or dash, may start with a digit)."
msgstr ""
" Ren'Py は Transform 内部での sampler2D 型の uniform をサポートするようになりました。これらは sample テクスチャに設定されるテクス"
"チャです。これらの transform には displayable や displayable になる文字列が供給されます。"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:151
msgid "In places where the syntax allowed the ``at`` keyword, it now allows an ``at transform:`` block."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:153
msgid ""
"In places where a displayable is expected, it is now possible to use an ``image:`` block, and to define an ATL image, like an "
"anonymous :ref:`atl-image-statement`."
msgstr ""

